<subSubSection id="5CBC6559187EFFE8FF35FBF54A57FADD" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="141936D2187EFFE8FF35FBF54A57FADD" blockId="9.[151,1437,438,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC0187EFFE8FF35FBF5490FFBAD" bold="true" box="[199,308,1122,1147]" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be readily recognised by the strongly anteriorly recurved row of macrosetae on the subgenital plates and by the arms of the aedeagal ventral process angularly bent at a right angle at midlength. Among the Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D51187EFFE8FE74FB3C49C1FB14" box="[390,506,1195,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC0187EFFE8FE74FB3C49C1FB14" box="[390,506,1195,1218]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">Signoretia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only this and 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D51187EFFE8FD59FB3C4B33FB14" box="[683,776,1195,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC0187EFFE8FD59FB3C4B33FB14" box="[683,776,1195,1218]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">S. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the ventral process of the pygofer very short. In 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D51187EFFE8FA75FB3C48EEFB30" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC0187EFFE8FA75FB3C48EEFB30" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">S. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ventral pygofer process is broad, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D51187EFFE8FCF4FB584BBEFB30" box="[774,901,1230,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similaris">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC0187EFFE8FCF4FB584BBEFB30" box="[774,901,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="495">S. similaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is short, spiculate, spine-like and the aedeagi of these two species are entirely different.
</paragraph>
